lead_paragraph: J.T. Miller scored twice in the second period and Henrik Lundqvist made 30 saves to lead the New York Rangers to a 4-1 win over the Carolina Hurricanes on Friday night.

headline.main: Miller Scores Twice, Rangers Beat Hurricanes 4-1
